abstract: The strike on a car killed all five onboard, including a woman who had given birth hours before, relatives and officials said.
snippet: The strike on a car killed all five onboard, including a woman who had given birth hours before, relatives and officials said.
lead_paragraph: KHOST, Afghanistan — An American drone strike on a car carrying a woman who had just given birth in southeastern Afghanistan left five people dead, including the mother, three of her relatives and the driver, Afghan officials and family members said on Sunday.

abstract: Recordings have emerged of private conversations that Julian Assange, the WikiLeaks founder, had while living in the Ecuadorean Embassy. He and a Spanish prosecutor blame the United States.
snippet: Recordings have emerged of private conversations that Julian Assange, the WikiLeaks founder, had while living in the Ecuadorean Embassy. He and a Spanish prosecutor blame the United States.
lead_paragraph: MADRID — This much has become clear in recent weeks: When Julian Assange, the WikiLeaks founder, was living in Ecuador’s embassy in London, someone was spying on him, recording his private conversations. The question is: Who ordered the surveillance?

abstract: Miscalculations, and an unexpected victory by President Trump, have put abortion access at its most vulnerable point in decades, and the left on the defensive. Now it is trying to recover.
snippet: Miscalculations, and an unexpected victory by President Trump, have put abortion access at its most vulnerable point in decades, and the left on the defensive. Now it is trying to recover.
lead_paragraph: ATLANTA — The pin was small, and rusted on the back. Sharon Wood had packed it away in 1973 as a relic of a battle fought and won: the image of a black coat hanger, slashed out by a red line.

abstract: After years of American pressure, China is taking steps to shut off the illicit supply of deadly synthetic opioids. But don’t expect an end to the overdoses.
snippet: After years of American pressure, China is taking steps to shut off the illicit supply of deadly synthetic opioids. But don’t expect an end to the overdoses.
lead_paragraph: When things go wrong, those in power often promise to make it right. But do they? In this series, The Times investigates to see if those promises were kept.

abstract: Chief Petty Officer Edward Gallagher’s case pits a Pentagon hierarchy committed to enforcing longstanding rules of combat against a commander in chief with no military experience but a finely honed sense of grievance against authority.
snippet: Chief Petty Officer Edward Gallagher’s case pits a Pentagon hierarchy committed to enforcing longstanding rules of combat against a commander in chief with no military experience but a finely honed sense of grievance against authority.
lead_paragraph: He was limp and dusty from an explosion, conscious but barely. A far cry from the fierce, masked Islamic State fighters who once seized vast swaths of Iraq and Syria, the captive was a scraggly teenager in a tank top with limbs so thin that his watch slid easily off his wrist.

abstract: President Trump’s aides were delighted that news of his Thanksgiving Day visit to Afghanistan stayed under wraps.
snippet: President Trump’s aides were delighted that news of his Thanksgiving Day visit to Afghanistan stayed under wraps.
lead_paragraph: BAGRAM AIR FIELD, Afghanistan — It may be the leakiest White House in history. The news media has unearthed details of President Trump’s calls with foreign leaders, his candid assessments of senior aides and his private daily schedules.

lead_paragraph: Twitter suspended the accounts of Danielle Stella, a Republican candidate hoping to challenge Democratic Representative Ilhan Omar of Minnesota next year, after she suggested the congresswoman should be tried for treason and hanged.

abstract: The Democrats need a unifier. It could be the Vermont Socialist.
snippet: The Democrats need a unifier. It could be the Vermont Socialist.
lead_paragraph: The Democratic Party needs a nominee, but right now it has a train wreck instead. The front-runner seems too old for the job and is poised to lose the first two primary season contests. The woman who was supposed to become the front-runner on the basis of her policy chops is sliding in the polls after thoroughly botching her health care strategy.
